1
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:42,267
<i> Paz! Don't stoop to her level!</i>

2
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:43,500
<i> No, I have to.</i>

3
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:44,633
<i> She's a husband beater!</i>

4
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:47,033
<i>That shameless woman
is a child abuser!</i>

5
00:00:47,167 --> 00:00:48,467
<i>So now you're siding with Felma?</i>

6
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:49,767
<i>Seriously? You're all a bunch
of gullible idiots!</i>

7
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,067
<i> Why did you turn it off?</i>

8
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,133
<i>Hazel, can you please stop
ruining my wife's name?</i>

9
00:00:53,267 --> 00:00:54,633
<i> I'm your wife!</i>

10
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:57,200
<i> Come back to me with Jessica.</i>

11
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,267
<i> I'm giving you until tonight.</i>

12
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:01,733
<i>If you don't, we'll settle this
in court.</i>

13
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:03,933
<i>Manuel, why did you bring
so many people with you?</i>

14
00:01:04,067 --> 00:01:06,133
<i> Hazel, they're our lawyers.</i>

15
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:07,767
<i>We are here to advise you
on record</i>

16
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:11,500
<i>that your continued harassment,
defamation, and online slander</i>

17
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:15,033
<i>against our clients can and will
be met with full legal action.</i>

18
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:17,567
<i>Stop your false accusations
against Miss Ruiz</i>

19
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:21,800
<i>or she will have to file several
counter complaints against you.</i>

20
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:25,333
<i>If you'll file a kidnapping case
against Mr. Cruz and Miss Ruiz,</i>

21
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:27,300
<i> then we'll see you in court.</i>

22
00:01:27,433 --> 00:01:28,967
<i> I was fooled, Alice.</i>

23
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,700
<i>That's my daughter and husband.</i>

24
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:32,000
<i> They're my family!</i>

25
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:34,133
<i> Manuel, he's mine!</i>

26
00:01:34,267 --> 00:01:36,167
<i>Only I should benefit from him.</i>

27
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:37,200
<i> No one else!</i>

28
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:38,567
<i>- No one else!
- That's enough already!</i>

29
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:47,200
Jessica...

30
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:48,667
calm down.

31
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:51,367
For sure, mom and dad have some
good news when they come home.

32
00:01:53,233 --> 00:01:54,233
What's that, Sis?

33
00:01:56,067 --> 00:01:57,567
This?

34
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,567
My scrapbooks.

35
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:00,700
I'll take it to the storage room

36
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:02,867
because there's no more space
on the bookshelf.

37
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:07,600
You really love making
scrapbooks.

38
00:02:07,733 --> 00:02:09,733
It's cute.

39
00:02:09,867 --> 00:02:12,100
- May I see?
- Go!

40
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:29,567
You guys really had such a happy
relationship with Jeffrey

41
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:31,400
and Andrea, right?

42
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:36,167
But now they're mad at you
and Auntie Felma

43
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:37,867
because of me and dad.

44
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:40,800
Hey, don't worry.

45
00:02:40,933 --> 00:02:43,133
We're going to be okay.

46
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:44,533
All of us.

47
00:02:44,667 --> 00:02:46,967
We'll be one big happy family.

48
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,667
Was this your 18th birthday
party, Sis?

49
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,633
Yes.

50
00:02:56,767 --> 00:02:58,567
But I didn't want anything
too extravagant.

51
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:00,633
So we held it here.

52
00:03:00,767 --> 00:03:02,300
Simple.

53
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:03,567
Intimate.

54
00:03:04,667 --> 00:03:07,800
Just us and a few close guests.

55
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:09,400
At least you had one.

56
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:14,400
Hey, your birthday's coming up
soon, too!

57
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:16,567
You're about to have
your 18th birthday!

58
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:18,300
You knew?

59
00:03:18,433 --> 00:03:19,967
Of course.

60
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,700
You're my sister.

61
00:03:21,867 --> 00:03:24,033
When I talked to dad,

62
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:26,100
I asked a few things about you.

63
00:03:28,867 --> 00:03:34,500
You know, Coleen, I used to wish
for a big celebration

64
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:36,400
on my 18th birthday.

65
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,800
With family and friends, too.

66
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:42,400
But now...

67
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:46,400
not anymore.

68
00:03:46,533 --> 00:03:47,967
Why not?

69
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,267
Because my priorities
have changed.

70
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:53,400
I just want dad and me
to be stable,

71
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:55,867
and for us to fix our issues
with mom.

72
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:59,433
And for your family
to be okay, too.

73
00:04:03,633 --> 00:04:05,200
<i> Let's celebrate!</i>

74
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:08,533
Sure, let's do it, Dear.

75
00:04:08,667 --> 00:04:11,933
Mom, let's have it at the same
time as Jessica's birthday!

76
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:15,000
- Sure, we can do that.
- Let's make it

77
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:16,533
a surprise for her, Mom.

78
00:04:16,667 --> 00:04:18,100
Okay.

79
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:19,500
- Why?
- She's over there.

80
00:04:19,633 --> 00:04:22,233
Oh, wait, maybe we can...

81
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:24,700
just keep it small?
A simple gathering,

82
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:26,300
since our budget's tight.

83
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:28,700
- Dad.
- Manuel...

84
00:04:28,867 --> 00:04:30,700
I'll cover it.

85
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:32,400
It's not going to be
extravagant anyway.

86
00:04:32,533 --> 00:04:34,533
We could just do it
at a restaurant.

87
00:04:34,667 --> 00:04:36,200
Just us.

88
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:41,033
And maybe I can also invite
Jeff and Andrea.

89
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:42,700
Who knows? That might be
our chance

90
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:43,933
to finally make peace.

91
00:04:49,067 --> 00:04:50,833
What's going on?

92
00:04:50,967 --> 00:04:53,033
Did something go wrong during
your meetup with Mom?

93
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:56,400
Oh, Jessica, no.

94
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:59,967
Actually, the talk
with your mom went really well.

95
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,900
She won't be causing
any more trouble.

96
00:05:02,067 --> 00:05:03,733
Really, Sis?

97
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:07,467
Dad, mom won't be
bothering us anymore!

98
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,100
Thank you, Auntie Felma.

99
00:05:10,533 --> 00:05:12,100
Coleen!

100
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:19,933
So now you'll finally live
in peace and harmony

101
00:05:20,067 --> 00:05:22,167
because you've taken down Hazel?

102
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:25,367
But I'm still not at ease.

103
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:28,567
Something about that woman
still gives me a bad feeling.

104
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:30,400
It's like she's not done yet.

105
00:05:30,533 --> 00:05:33,100
Oh, friend, don't waste
your energy thinking about

106
00:05:33,233 --> 00:05:35,700
what stunt she'll pull next.

107
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:39,500
What matters now is focusing
on Jeff and Andrea.

108
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:41,900
They're the ones
who truly matter.

109
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:43,067
You're right, Sis.

110
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,733
I miss them, too.

111
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:47,967
I really hope they come

112
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:51,000
to Jessica's surprise
birthday party.

113
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:55,633
So we can all see each other
and finally talk things out.

114
00:05:55,767 --> 00:05:57,633
I hope so, too.

115
00:05:57,767 --> 00:06:01,267
Oh, by the way,
where's the party happening?

116
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,600
At Tala Diwa Kitchen.

117
00:06:04,767 --> 00:06:07,600
Sis, can I count on you
to give the invitation

118
00:06:07,767 --> 00:06:09,833
to Jeffrey and Andrea?

119
00:06:09,967 --> 00:06:11,833
Of course, Sis.

120
00:06:11,967 --> 00:06:13,200
- Come on, let's go.
- Thank you.

121
00:06:14,267 --> 00:06:15,900
Let's go to your office.

122
00:06:46,967 --> 00:06:48,100
Got any news?

123
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,967
I picked up some stocks
at FMP earlier.

124
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:53,800
I didn't have them delivered,

125
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:57,067
so, you know,
I could spy around a bit.

126
00:06:57,200 --> 00:07:00,267
And I found out something.

127
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,333
Go on.

128
00:07:01,467 --> 00:07:02,600
Tell me.

129
00:07:02,733 --> 00:07:08,867
Felma's planning a surprise
birthday party for Jessica.

130
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:17,867
So that woman really wants
to replace me...

131
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,433
as Jessica's mother.

132
00:07:23,733 --> 00:07:25,167
A surprise?

133
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:28,100
Fine...

134
00:07:28,233 --> 00:07:31,400
then I'll give them a surprise
they'll never forget.

135
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,433
This is the private room I found
at Tala Diwa Kitchen.

136
00:07:41,567 --> 00:07:42,900
Oh wow, it's beautiful.

137
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:44,300
This will be so easy
to decorate!

138
00:07:44,433 --> 00:07:45,733
Look at it, Darling.

139
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:47,233
Yes, it's beautiful.

140
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,933
You seem more excited than
anyone else.

141
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:53,567
Why? Am I not allowed
to cooperate?

142
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,500
It's beautiful.

143
00:07:55,633 --> 00:07:57,967
So, what's your motif?

144
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,067
White, Auntie.

145
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:05,667
Because it symbolizes peace,
acceptance, and sincerity.

146
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:08,567
That's how we want to welcome
Jessica into the family.

147
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:13,900
But the thing is,
as we welcome someone in,

148
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:16,200
we also lose two people
along the way.

149
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:26,300
Don't be sad, Dear.

150
00:08:26,433 --> 00:08:29,700
Who knows? Your siblings might
show up at the party.

151
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:34,267
We might finally talk
make peace.

152
00:08:35,433 --> 00:08:37,133
And...

153
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:39,367
maybe we can all
go home together.

154
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,067
I really hope so, Mom.

155
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:45,100
Because I don't like
this feeling.

156
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:48,400
I'm not used to us being apart
from them.

157
00:08:54,733 --> 00:08:58,233
So, I'll be in charge
of the decorations.

158
00:08:58,367 --> 00:09:02,633
I'm going to fill the whole
venue with white flowers.

159
00:09:02,767 --> 00:09:04,433
Thank you so much, Paz.

160
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,067
Come on, Paz.

161
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,600
- Ling.
- What?

162
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:13,100
Are you still mad at Manuel?

163
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:15,267
Felma has already forgiven him.

164
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,100
Well, I'm not Felma.

165
00:09:17,233 --> 00:09:19,233
She's a good person
and I'm not.

166
00:09:19,367 --> 00:09:21,200
Hey, Manuel!

167
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:25,167
Don't expect us to be all buddy
like before.

168
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:27,133
I'm doing this for...

169
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,433
your child.

170
00:09:29,667 --> 00:09:31,167
Then why did the conversation
suddenly shift to me?

171
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:33,000
Weren't we supposed to be
planning the party?

172
00:09:33,133 --> 00:09:34,333
You know, for fun?

173
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:36,333
Party, party, party, party!

174
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:40,300
That'll definitely bring out
my charm.

175
00:09:40,433 --> 00:09:41,700
Don't I have a white blazer?

176
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:43,500
Yes, it's there. I just tucked
it away in the cabinet.

177
00:09:43,633 --> 00:09:45,733
The one you used before
for the movie shoot.

178
00:09:45,867 --> 00:09:47,333
That one fits perfectly.

179
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:48,633
Movie shoot?

180
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:50,267
You did some filming
before, Uncle?

181
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,433
- Yes.
- What role did you play in?

182
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:53,567
He was lying in a coffin.

183
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,967
They shut the coffin door on him

184
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:57,400
because he kept winking
like crazy.

185
00:09:57,533 --> 00:09:58,433
The director went mad.

186
00:09:58,567 --> 00:09:59,700
It was shut!

187
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,567
Was he winking at him?

188
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:06,633
How did the winking go?

189
00:10:08,367 --> 00:10:10,167
Wait, wait.

190
00:10:12,433 --> 00:10:13,933
Come in, come in.

191
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,900
What now?

192
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:27,333
- How have you been?
- You're really back!

193
00:10:27,467 --> 00:10:29,100
Hold on. hold on, I'm good.

194
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:30,500
But how about you?
What happened?

195
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:31,933
Tell me everything.

196
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:33,367
- Oh, my.
- How did it go?

197
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,067
No one told me anything!

198
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:36,633
I thought it was just
an interview.

199
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:38,533
Turns out, there was a skills
and knowledge test

200
00:10:38,667 --> 00:10:40,333
before the panel interview!

201
00:10:40,467 --> 00:10:42,367
Why? Did you have a hard time?

202
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,833
A lot, I wasn't prepared at all.

203
00:10:44,967 --> 00:10:47,200
They asked me about medical
stuff, surgical nursing,

204
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,000
the infection control,

205
00:10:49,133 --> 00:10:53,200
emergency response,
then pharmacology...

206
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:55,033
Can you imagine? It was crazy!

207
00:10:55,167 --> 00:10:58,033
But you passed everything
with flying colors, right?

208
00:10:58,167 --> 00:11:00,000
I was just pretending
to check on you,

209
00:11:00,133 --> 00:11:01,867
but honestly, Franz already
called me.

210
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,133
I already know the results.

211
00:11:04,267 --> 00:11:05,800
So impressive.

212
00:11:05,933 --> 00:11:09,200
You aced the panel interview
and the exam.

213
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:10,633
It was a piece of cake for you.

214
00:11:10,767 --> 00:11:16,133
I even told them to make it
tough for you, but nothing.

215
00:11:16,267 --> 00:11:19,133
What? You deliberately made it
harder for me?

216
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,867
Of course! Right?

217
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:24,500
You beat me in almost every
subject back in college.

218
00:11:24,633 --> 00:11:26,933
Do you think I'd just let
that slide?

219
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:29,500
You're really something else!

220
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:30,733
Of course!

221
00:11:30,867 --> 00:11:33,967
Wait, welcome to Southcrest
Premier Hospital.

222
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,167
We're now together!

223
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:39,100
- I'm so happy!
- Thank you, Sis.

224
00:11:39,233 --> 00:11:40,567
But I'm sorry.

225
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,533
There's no opening yet
for a head nurse.

226
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:44,500
- Oh, come on.
- That position

227
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:45,667
really suits you.

228
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,000
You're also qualified for it.

229
00:11:47,133 --> 00:11:49,000
It's okay. The offer was good.

230
00:11:49,133 --> 00:11:51,567
Come on, like I'd say no?
Or even complain?

231
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:53,733
But seriously, I really
appreciate everything

232
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:54,733
you did for me.

233
00:11:54,867 --> 00:11:56,000
Thank you so much, Sis.

234
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:56,867
Thank you, thank you.

235
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,000
You are most welcome.

236
00:12:00,867 --> 00:12:01,733
Well, what now?

237
00:12:01,867 --> 00:12:03,100
I'm your boss now.

238
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,233
Enjoy it while it lasts.

239
00:12:05,367 --> 00:12:07,167
Because who knows,

240
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:08,933
I might take your position next.

241
00:12:09,067 --> 00:12:10,900
There's nothing I can do about
it if it happens.

242
00:12:11,033 --> 00:12:12,100
Oh, yes?

243
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:13,500
Try me.

244
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:17,633
I'm just happy you're here!

245
00:12:26,933 --> 00:12:27,933
Hey...

246
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:31,700
Are you okay, Jeff?
What happened to you?

247
00:12:31,833 --> 00:12:33,533
Mom and Coleen are really
something else.

248
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,867
Why? What did they do?

249
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,633
They're throwing a party
for that Jessica?

250
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:59,500
Did mom and Coleen assume that
we're going to attend?

251
00:13:02,167 --> 00:13:03,767
We're her real children.

252
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:07,933
And now they're throwing a party
for someone else's daughter?

253
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:11,067
And now what? We're just guests?

254
00:13:12,067 --> 00:13:13,600
That's so disrespectful, Jeff!

255
00:13:14,633 --> 00:13:16,067
That's not what she intended,
apparently.

256
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,667
Auntis Paz said mom invited us

257
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:21,300
because she wants everyone to be
together to talk things out.

258
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,033
I'll only talk to mom

259
00:13:25,767 --> 00:13:31,167
once that man is out of our
house and out of our lives.

260
00:13:48,967 --> 00:13:51,133
Rona, Didang,
how about this one?

261
00:13:51,267 --> 00:13:52,367
Oh, no!

262
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:54,100
You look old in that.

263
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:56,133
Don't wear that.
Unless I'm the one wearing it!

264
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:57,400
You're so silly, Didang.

265
00:13:57,533 --> 00:13:59,200
Didang.

266
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:00,433
How about this one?

267
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:05,400
I really don't like it, Bestie.

268
00:14:05,533 --> 00:14:07,300
This is stressing me out.

269
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:09,300
I seriously don't know
what to wear.

270
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:12,233
And Jessica, she's so petite!

271
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:16,300
Oh! But, Bestie,
you guys are amazing.

272
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:18,100
Jessica really has no idea?

273
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:19,267
None at all.

274
00:14:19,633 --> 00:14:21,667
While we were planning
the party,

275
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:25,000
we made sure Jessica went with
Didang to the grocery store.

276
00:14:25,133 --> 00:14:26,400
Oh, yes, that's true.

277
00:14:26,533 --> 00:14:29,300
Well, unless Didang slipped up.

278
00:14:29,467 --> 00:14:31,267
- Hey!
- She always does that!

279
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,267
Hey!

280
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,467
That's so unfair, Coleen!

281
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:37,233
I haven't said anything
to Jessica...

282
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:39,000
- Yet!
- Yet!

283
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:41,600
Didang, I think I heard my name.

284
00:14:41,733 --> 00:14:43,433
What is it that you're not
telling me?

285
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,267
The longanisa and tocino
are ready for pickup.

286
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:57,767
The sisig won't be available
until tomorrow.

287
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,933
Meet this at the terminal, okay?

288
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:01,833
So you can sell them
right away, got it?

289
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,333
Oh, Okay, okay. Bye.

290
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:07,433
Hi!

291
00:15:08,467 --> 00:15:09,433
Hey...

292
00:15:12,267 --> 00:15:13,500
Yuck! What's that...

293
00:15:13,633 --> 00:15:16,300
Can you please get rid of
Felma's frozen cadavers already?

294
00:15:16,433 --> 00:15:18,200
Hurry! Ew, gross!

295
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:20,167
Don't complain, friend.

296
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:21,100
You're the one who suggested

297
00:15:21,233 --> 00:15:22,600
I turn this into a business,
remember?

298
00:15:25,567 --> 00:15:27,700
Wow!

299
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:30,033
Signature!

300
00:15:31,967 --> 00:15:34,000
I thought you were
on a tight budget?

301
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,100
Why did you even buy
from an expensive boutique

302
00:15:36,267 --> 00:15:39,100
just to dress up
for Jessica's debut?

303
00:15:40,067 --> 00:15:41,833
Let me guess,

304
00:15:41,967 --> 00:15:44,000
you maxed out your credit card,
didn't you?

305
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,733
Well, yes.

306
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:48,767
But it's fine,
I can pay it off now.

307
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:50,233
I got a job!

308
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:54,333
You have work already?
You got accepted?

309
00:15:54,467 --> 00:15:56,500
That's what I just said, right?
I have a job now!

310
00:15:56,633 --> 00:15:57,500
What? Wait.

311
00:15:57,633 --> 00:15:59,533
What's that? You smell
like longanisa!

312
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:00,933
Girl, go wash your hands first!

313
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:02,233
- You're so mean.
- Of course, right?

314
00:16:02,367 --> 00:16:08,033
I have to look drop dead divine
on my daughter's debut.

315
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:11,833
After all, I'm the mother
of the debutant.

316
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,300
Ready to slay.

317
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:16,667
More than ready.

318
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:21,067
Didang, I heard you say
my name earlier.

319
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:23,300
What is it
you're not telling me?

320
00:16:23,433 --> 00:16:26,433
Didang, I definitely
heard my name.

321
00:16:26,567 --> 00:16:28,200
- What was that?
- The party!

322
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:30,200
- Oh, I just spoiled it!
- What party?

323
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:32,067
- My party!
- Mine!

324
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,167
My party.

325
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:34,633
- My party.
- Yes.

326
00:16:34,767 --> 00:16:36,567
- Rona's birthday party.
- Party?

327
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:37,800
She said, you should come.

328
00:16:37,933 --> 00:16:39,267
- Yes.
- Oh, really?

329
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,333
That's right.

330
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:42,667
Thank you, Rona.

331
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:44,433
So I'm invited.

332
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:46,367
Rona, when's the party?

333
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,600
Tomorrow.

334
00:16:47,733 --> 00:16:50,433
Wait, we have the same birthday?

335
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:53,933
- We have the same birthday!
- We have the same birthday!

336
00:16:54,067 --> 00:16:55,700
- You share the same birthday.
- Yes! I totally forgot.

337
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:58,800
You do share the same birthday,
I totally forgot.

338
00:16:58,933 --> 00:17:00,200
- Sorry, sorry!
- Didang.

339
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:01,400
Didang.

340
00:17:01,533 --> 00:17:03,400
But it's okay. Rona's
celebration is in the evening,

341
00:17:03,533 --> 00:17:06,167
so we'll have yours
in the afternoon, right here.

342
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,433
Yes.

343
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:09,433
You should come.

344
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:10,667
- Come with your sister.
- Yes, Rona.

345
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,067
- Yes, Rona.
- Happy birthday

346
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,333
to both of you.

347
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:16,933
But, Coleen,
I don't have a dress.

348
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:18,700
Come on, it's okay.

349
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:21,067
I have a lot of dresses here
that would fit you.

350
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:23,400
There are more in the closet,
some I haven't even worn.

351
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:25,333
- Oh, there it is.
- Thank you, Coleen.

352
00:17:25,467 --> 00:17:28,067
Come on, let's go
check them out.

353
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,433
Let's go, Jessica.

354
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,900
Okay, guys, let's move faster

355
00:17:33,033 --> 00:17:34,467
so you can get some rest after.

356
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:37,567
Wait a second, Felma,
we're almost done.

357
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:41,333
- Ta-da!
- Okay.

358
00:17:41,467 --> 00:17:42,333
Did you like it?

359
00:17:42,467 --> 00:17:43,933
Of course!
It's beautiful.

360
00:17:44,067 --> 00:17:45,667
Thank you, Sis.

361
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,133
You're welcome, Sis.

362
00:17:47,267 --> 00:17:49,467
Wait, everyone, can you please
come here?

363
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,700
I just want to remind
everyone that

364
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:55,567
this is a surprise birthday
party for Jessica.

365
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,233
No one says anything,
no spoilers, okay?

366
00:17:58,367 --> 00:17:59,233
Yes, Ma'am.

367
00:17:59,367 --> 00:18:02,033
- Sis, promise me, okay?
- Oh?

368
00:18:02,167 --> 00:18:04,733
No one says a word.
It's a total secret.

369
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:06,300
Sis, you better be treating us
to dinner!

370
00:18:06,433 --> 00:18:07,433
Okay, I will.

371
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:08,833
Okay, let's have dinner.

372
00:18:08,967 --> 00:18:11,200
Come on. Turn off the lights,
okay?

373
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:12,267
Thank you.

374
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,567
Thank you, everyone.

375
00:18:14,767 --> 00:18:17,300
Don't forget the lights.

376
00:18:17,433 --> 00:18:18,967
Thank you, guys.

377
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:47,100
I should be the one throwing you
a party, my dear...

378
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:50,500
not Felma.

379
00:19:00,933 --> 00:19:05,467
<i>- Happy birthday to you!
- Happy birthday to you!</i>

380
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:07,733
Jessica,

381
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:09,533
make a wish
and then blow the candle.

382
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:24,533
- Yes! Come on, let's eat.
- Yes!

383
00:19:24,667 --> 00:19:26,400
Didang, thank you.

384
00:19:26,533 --> 00:19:28,200
You're welcome.

385
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:29,633
Thank you so much, Dad.

386
00:19:29,767 --> 00:19:32,267
Coleen, thank you.

387
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:37,167
And of course, Auntie Felma,
thank you so much.

388
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:38,967
You're welcome.

389
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:40,200
Go on and eat.

390
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:42,900
You still have to go to Rona's
birthday party, remember?

391
00:19:43,033 --> 00:19:45,000
Yes, Didang, I'll just have one
slice of pizza

392
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:46,800
because I'll be eating
at the party.

393
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:48,467
Coleen, I'll just eat one piece
of chicken.

394
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:51,333
Why don't you just skip
eating now?

395
00:19:51,467 --> 00:19:53,533
Since you've already blown out
the candle

396
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:55,400
and celebrated your birthday,

397
00:19:55,533 --> 00:19:56,867
that should be enough, right?

398
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,467
Oh yes, true!

399
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,700
And besides, you really need
to leave now.

400
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,733
You're still going to the salon,

401
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:05,100
and that'll take a while.

402
00:20:05,233 --> 00:20:06,367
So better head out.

403
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:07,500
Yeah, you're right, Mom.

404
00:20:07,633 --> 00:20:09,567
- Come on, Jessica.
- Okay then.

405
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:11,133
- Oh, take care..
- Oh, okay, okay.

406
00:20:11,267 --> 00:20:13,167
- Bye, Dad!
- Be safe, be safe.

407
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:15,833
- Bye, Dad!
- Oh, See them out.

408
00:20:15,967 --> 00:20:17,267
- Let's go, Jessica.
- Be safe.

409
00:20:19,867 --> 00:20:22,033
Check your stuff, you might
forget something.

410
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,167
We will!

411
00:20:27,867 --> 00:20:29,833
There! Take care!

412
00:20:29,967 --> 00:20:31,600
Thank you.
Friend, come on.

413
00:20:31,733 --> 00:20:33,433
Your godchildren
have already left.

414
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:35,400
Oh, wait. Sis, let me see
your makeup?

415
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:37,033
- What? Why?
- Oh, it's already flawless

416
00:20:37,167 --> 00:20:38,767
Just a little retouch needed.

417
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:40,367
- Yes, just a little retouch.
- How about you, guys?

418
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:41,300
Fix this one up, too.

419
00:20:41,433 --> 00:20:42,200
You've got to make him
look handsome

420
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:43,300
because he's giving a speech
later.

421
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:45,333
I got this.

422
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:47,400
Still smirking,
Oh, faster! Faster!

423
00:20:47,533 --> 00:20:49,533
Go, go, go! We should get
to the venue early.

424
00:20:49,667 --> 00:20:51,167
- Wait, wait.
- There you go.

425
00:20:54,767 --> 00:20:55,800
I don't know.
Just leave it to you.

426
00:20:55,933 --> 00:20:57,233
Oh yeah, I'm gonna do my own
makeup.

427
00:20:57,367 --> 00:20:59,367
I can do makeup while eating.
I got this.

428
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:02,033
- Grease might get on your...
- Hey, Sis.

429
00:21:02,167 --> 00:21:04,533
Are Andeng and Jeff coming?

430
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:07,433
Oh, I texted them last night
and this morning,

431
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:08,667
but...

432
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:09,833
no reply yet.

433
00:21:11,667 --> 00:21:12,633
Oh, really?

434
00:21:12,767 --> 00:21:13,833
Call them, call them.

435
00:21:14,767 --> 00:21:15,567
You want me to call them?

436
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:16,433
They're not even answering
my calls.

437
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:18,400
Just call them!

438
00:21:18,533 --> 00:21:20,733
Okay, I will.

439
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:21,867
You might choke on your food.

440
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,533
No! Oh, wait.

441
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:26,500
- Oh, you want juice?
- Juice.

442
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:28,600
His phone is off.

443
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:31,067
Then text them,
text them.

444
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:32,133
I'll try calling Andrea.

445
00:21:32,267 --> 00:21:34,067
- Yes.
- I'll try Andrea.

446
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:37,700
Her phone is busy.

447
00:21:43,533 --> 00:21:45,733
They gave me hope, Mayette.

448
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:50,733
During the final interview...

449
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:52,467
they were practically singing
my praises.

450
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:53,800
I mean, they couldn't stop
complimenting me.

451
00:21:55,133 --> 00:21:56,633
I even heard...

452
00:21:56,767 --> 00:22:01,367
the side comments of the panel
over the conference call.

453
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:04,600
They were even saying,
"She's the one."

454
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:12,833
And then, after all that,
they emailed me.

455
00:22:16,733 --> 00:22:18,833
Turns out, I didn't get the job.

456
00:22:18,967 --> 00:22:23,967
Because the boss wanted
a male virtual assistant.

457
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:26,467
Can you believe that?
It's so annoying!

458
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,500
Totally unfair!

459
00:22:28,633 --> 00:22:30,067
So sexist!

460
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:56,067
Are you going somewhere?

461
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,400
We...

462
00:22:57,533 --> 00:22:58,800
We're going to Jessica's party.

463
00:23:00,833 --> 00:23:01,867
We're not going.

464
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:07,300
Jeff, come on,
do it for your mom.

465
00:23:07,433 --> 00:23:08,533
No!

466
00:23:10,067 --> 00:23:11,233
Oh, sorry, Dad.

467
00:23:11,367 --> 00:23:14,300
Mom and I thought
we were all going.

468
00:23:14,433 --> 00:23:17,067
So you could talk
to Mommy Pretty.

469
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:19,100
Maybe start fixing things
between you two?

470
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,800
I'm sorry, Sweetie.

471
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,600
Your Auntie Andrea and I
are just not ready

472
00:23:24,733 --> 00:23:26,300
to face mom yet.

473
00:23:26,433 --> 00:23:27,900
It's okay.

474
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:29,867
I understand, Dad.

475
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:32,000
We can't really force it.

476
00:23:32,133 --> 00:23:33,767
No worries.

477
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:35,933
All right, Dad,
I'll just go get changed.

478
00:23:42,833 --> 00:23:44,700
Do you even know how excited
your daughter is?

479
00:23:47,133 --> 00:23:49,333
She rarely gets to go
to parties.

480
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,533
Daisy, you understand me, right?

481
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,567
I get that you're upset, yes.

482
00:23:57,700 --> 00:23:59,567
But what I don't understand is

483
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:01,000
why you're dragging the kid
into this.

484
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:03,200
So...

485
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:05,367
should I keep ironing this
or what?

486
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:12,833
Mayette, sorry...

487
00:24:14,067 --> 00:24:15,567
for the bother.

488
00:24:18,833 --> 00:24:21,233
I just don't have anyone else
to talk to.

489
00:24:25,733 --> 00:24:30,200
Whenever I have problems
like this,

490
00:24:35,767 --> 00:24:38,300
I usually talk to mom.

491
00:24:41,333 --> 00:24:43,467
Sorry for bothering you.

492
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:52,400
Thank you for listening to me.

493
00:24:54,300 --> 00:24:55,267
All right then.

494
00:24:58,933 --> 00:25:00,467
Thank you.

495
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:01,800
Bye.

496
00:25:17,733 --> 00:25:18,967
<i> Andrea, please.</i>

497
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:21,667
<i> Go to Jessica's party.</i>

498
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:23,033
<i> Please, Dear.</i>

499
00:25:36,033 --> 00:25:37,900
All thanks to Coleen.

500
00:25:38,033 --> 00:25:40,400
It was all her idea.

501
00:25:40,533 --> 00:25:45,167
And of course ,Dad,
for always being there for me.

502
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:47,667
My dad is a cheater.

503
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,267
He left us for another woman,

504
00:25:49,400 --> 00:25:51,100
married her,

505
00:25:51,233 --> 00:25:52,767
and then just abandoned us.

506
00:25:53,033 --> 00:25:56,633
But despite everything I did,

507
00:25:56,767 --> 00:25:58,767
she still forgave me.

508
00:25:58,900 --> 00:26:02,667
I hope Jeffrey and Andrea
can forgive me as well.

509
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:05,400
Auntie Coleen,
why are you crying?

510
00:26:05,533 --> 00:26:08,133
I'm just happy
for your Auntie Jessica, Tetay.

511
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,267
I wish every girl could dance

512
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,567
with her father at her party
like that.

513
00:26:10,700 --> 00:26:13,633
What are mom and Coleen
up to now?

514
00:26:13,767 --> 00:26:18,267
They're celebrating
Dad's kid's birthday.

515
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,267
My only prayer now...

516
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:22,800
is for respect to come back.

517
00:26:22,933 --> 00:26:27,500
I hope we don't lose the trust
we have in each other...

518
00:26:27,633 --> 00:26:29,667
as friends.

519
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:31,667
Friends?
